    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-10-21T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-10-21T20:00:00-05:00" n="700"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d700">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.243/10–2247: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-10-22T10:00:00+09:00"
                            >October 22, 1947—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 21—11:34 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2112. Minister of Communications<note n="80" xml:id="d700fn1">Gen. Yu
                        Ta-wei.</note> has made request to Ambassador that spare parts et cetera in
                    group program be sold by FLC to Ministry at 10 cents on dollar (refEmbtel 1902,
                    September 14 [<hi rend="italic">11</hi>], 4 p.m.) Col. Ivy of FLC is informing
                    Washington further regarding his discussions with Ministry.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
